						               													<description>Pack of Crooks is a semi-cooperative deckbuilding card game with a twist. Work as a team to pull off heists, then fight for the loot!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In Pack of Crooks, players are crooks who are working to complete jobs and collect loot. &amp;#10;To successfully complete jobs, you will need to work with a bunch of other crooks. &amp;#10;Your objective is to finish the game with the most loot.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;To do this, you will need to purchase tool cards to build your own personal deck. &amp;#10;You will then use the cards in your hand to defeat the security in each room and negotiate for your share of the loot.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;To beat each security card, players must play tool cards of the same color to equal or higher value. &amp;#10;For example, a Vault is a purple security card with a value of 20. Players will need to combine 20 points of purple tool cards. &amp;#10;Players will need to negotiate to decide who will defeat each room card, and how the loot will be split. The combination of players that can play the most points wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game is finished when all jobs are complete. Players should count their loot. &amp;#10;Their tool cards are also worth the value they were purchased for. &amp;#10;Cards from a player&amp;rsquo;s starting hand have no value.&amp;#10;The winner is the player with the highest total.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;-description from publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
